This article is a statement made by the President on the 42nd anniversary of the Roe v. Wade Supreme Court ruling. The President expresses his commitment to protecting a woman's freedom to make choices about her body and health, and emphasizes the importance of government not interfering in private family matters. He opposes efforts, such as the bill H.R. 7, that would restrict women's reproductive freedom and access to healthcare. The President also highlights the importance of reducing unintended pregnancies, supporting maternal and child health, promoting adoptions, and minimizing the need for abortion. He calls for the equal rights, freedoms, and opportunities for both daughters and sons.